Description: Identifying string linked to a particular sample or specimen, provide by the data contributor
The data file provides the name of the raw file generated by the instrument. The data files can be instrument raw files but also converted peak lists such as mzML, MGF or result files like mzIdentML.
Identifying string linked to the individual or animal being studied, provided by the data contributor
The subject's age at the time of specimen extraction is the individual's age (since birth) at the time a given specimen was extracted. Measured as age in years.
The calculated age of the sample, measurement is determined or coded by the data contributor.

Description: Unique identifier for the study, assigned by the DCC
Name of the field center
Indicate which longitudinal visit for the individual the data comes from, provided by the data contributor's data dictionary
Indicate the geographic region for the individual (shown as ex. "840")
Indicate the consent group for the individual, provided by the data contributor's data dictionary
The taxonomic ranking including both species and subspecies the individual belongs to.
The biological sex of the individual
Race of individual
Valid Values: White,Black or African American,Asian,American Indian or Alaska Native,Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander,Multiracial,Other race,Prefer not to answer,Unknown,Not collected,Not applicable

Description: Ethnicity of individual
Valid Values: Not Hispanic or latino,Hispanic or latino,Prefer not to answer,Other,Unknown,Not collected,Not applicable

Description: A coded value specifying the self-declared ethnic origination independent of racial origination, provided by the data contributor's data dictionary
Age of the individual (age in years of the individual at first recorded study event (enrollment, visit, observation, sample collection, survey completion, etc.)
Whether the individual has been diagnosed with a condition or disease (physical and/or cognitive), "True" indicates the individual has been diagnosed
Indicate the disease or condition.
Taxonomic identifier. The National Center for Biotechnology Information taxon ID (formatted as, ex. "txid9989")
The scientific name of the species (typically a taxonomic group, ex. "Eremophila alpestris") the individual belongs to.
The biological species common name the individual belongs to (ex. "Horned Lark").note: As a default, the valid scientific name for the species should be indicated.
The life stage of the individual. note: Other are possible depending on life stage terminology for individual species. Please let the data curation team know.
Age of individual (formatted in months, ex. "72 months"). note: Uncertainty about the age might require recording age by specifying a lower and upper estimate in months for the age of the animal.

The status of the individual with regard to captivity. note: Wild, captive, and stranded values are applicable, especially for marine mammals. Depending on life stage terminology for individual species, other are possible. Please let the data curation team know.
The duration of captivity in months for the individuals in captivity (formatted in months, ex. 72 months). note: Applicable only to animals with captivity status captive.
